<!-- INSIGHTS -->
<section id="insights">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">Cross-Project Analysis</div>
    <h2>What Everyone Gets Wrong</h2>
    <div class="insights-grid">

      <div class="insight-card accent-rose">
        <div class="insight-icon">⚠️</div>
        <h3>PHPStan: Checkbox, Not Gate</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:12px">9 of 11 projects have PHPStan. Only 2 use it honestly.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>subscriptionify: level max, zero blanket suppressions</li>
          <li>koel: level 5 with targeted, commented ignores</li>
          <li>invoiceninja suppresses "Call to undefined method" — in a financial app</li>
          <li>akaunting: no phpstan.neon exists, despite handling taxes and reconciliation</li>
          <li>The pattern: PHPStan is added to composer.json, configured at whatever level passes, and never blocks a merge</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-card accent-amber">
        <div class="insight-icon">🏛️</div>
        <h3>God Classes Never Die — They Move</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:12px">The fat controller died. The 4,894-line job class lives on.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>coolify ApplicationDeploymentJob: 4,894 LOC — Git, Docker, Nixpacks, health checks, rollback in one class</li>
          <li>invoiceninja PdfBuilder: 2,410 LOC — the Action pattern didn't reach here</li>
          <li>bagisto Cart.php: 1,204 LOC, zero test coverage</li>
          <li>invoiceninja BaseRepository::alternativeSave(): 444 lines in a single method</li>
          <li>Decomposition requires discipline at every layer — one pattern can't solve it</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-card accent-rose">
        <div class="insight-icon">🔓</div>
        <h3>Security Advisories Suppressed in Financial Apps</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:12px">The most serious finding in this corpus.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong style="color:var(--rose)">akaunting</strong>: 22 Packagist security advisories suppressed with block-insecure: false — an accounting application</li>
          <li><strong style="color:var(--amber)">october</strong>: advisories block explicitly disabled</li>
          <li><strong style="color:var(--rose)">laraowl</strong>: VerifyLaraowlToken compares API tokens in plaintext — timing attack vulnerability</li>
          <li>Short-term fix ("it blocked our install") becomes permanent policy</li>
          <li>Vendor forking in akaunting's override/ means upstream security patches don't automatically apply</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-card accent-emerald">
        <div class="insight-icon">📈</div>
        <h3>What the Top Three Did Differently</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:12px">koel (8.70), subscriptionify (8.20), and monica (7.95) share three practices the rest don't.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Zero global helper function files — everything injectable via the container</li>
          <li>readonly final Value Objects / DTOs with private constructors and static make()</li>
          <li>PHPStan run at a level that actually enforces — not a level chosen because it passes</li>
          <li>koel uniquely has a CLAUDE.md that encodes architecture as refusable rules, not prose documentation</li>
          <li>All three use vertical-slice or feature-folder organisation rather than flat Laravel scaffolding</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-card accent-blue">
        <div class="insight-icon">🧩</div>
        <h3>Patterns Converging Across the Ecosystem</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:12px">What's becoming the new normal in serious Laravel codebases.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Action classes (lorisleiva/laravel-actions) replacing fat controllers — now mainstream</li>
          <li>AI integration as first-class: koel (app/Ai/), coolify (laravel/mcp), bagisto (laravel/ai 0.2.2)</li>
          <li>Inertia.js + Vue/React replacing Blade for data-heavy UIs</li>
          <li>Repository pattern is table stakes, not an architectural decision anymore</li>
          <li>Vertical-slice (DDD-inspired) over flat MVC is the emerging separator between top and middle tier</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-card accent-amber">
        <div class="insight-icon">📦</div>
        <h3>Package Constraints Force Better Design</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:12px">subscriptionify at 5K LOC scores higher than most full applications.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Package development forces interface contracts — you can't know what the host app looks like</li>
          <li>Injectable dependencies, config-driven behaviour, testability in isolation are requirements, not choices</li>
          <li>Full application developers avoid these decisions because they don't have to — and the debt accumulates</li>
          <li>PHPStan density of 119/KLOC for subscriptionify reflects framework-magic reliance in an isolated context, not poor quality</li>
          <li>Building a package before a feature is a useful architectural forcing function</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

